§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ What is the multiplicative inverse of $\eqc{(a, b)}$ in the
    rationals? ⦉
⦉

§ Result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ The multiplicative inverse of $\eqc{(a, b)} ∈ 𝗤$ if $b ≠
    0_{𝗭}$ is $\eqc{(b,a)}$. ⦉
</statement>

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the multiplicative inverse of $q ∈ 𝗤$ by
    $\inv{q}$. ⦉

  ‖ We denote $q · (\inv{r})$ by $q/r$. ⦉
⦉

§§ Division ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We call the operation $(a, b) ↦ a/b$ ❬rational division❭. ⦉
⦉

